250 g Ground Turkey
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
¼ cup Roasted Pepper Pesto
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
56 g Baby Spinach
2 tbsp Garlic Spread
2 tbsp Caesar Dressing
28 g Croutons
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Core, then cut peppers into 1/4-inch strips.
Spread garlic spread onto cut sides of buns. Transfer buns to a foil-lined baking sheet. Set aside.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then turkey and peppers. Cook, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Add roasted pepper pesto. Cook, stirring until coated, 1 min.

Top cut sides of buns with turkey mixture. Sprinkle mozzarella over top.
Broil in the middle of the oven until cheese is golden brown and melted, 2-3 min.

Add spinach, croutons and Caesar dressing to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Divide salad and open-faced turkey sandos between plates.

If you've opted to get turkey, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the sausage.